steam condensation required to obtain this amount of temperature change for 1,000 lpm of water is ap roximately 3 kg/s, equivalent to an energy exchange of about 1.67 x 10 % Cal/s, or 7MW.
The amount of steam and hot gases discharging directly to the atmosphere is unknown, but is probably at least as much as that being condensed at the ground surface.
