Reservoir properties The high flux of steam, the large area of intense hydrothermal alteration, and the associated occurrence of boiling low-chloride acidsulfate springs are all evidence for the presence of at least a shallow vapor-dominated system.
The source of steam and hot gases could be a deeper vapor-dominated system or perhaps a deep, subsurface boiling-hotwater convective system.
