Comments The thermal waters probably result from the deep circulation of surface waters (including possibly seawater) along fractures associated with the dike intrusions in the area.
Depth of circulation would reach 1.5 to 2.5 km if thermal gradients of 30 to 50Â°C/km are assumed.
The remoteness, low discharge, and low temperature of the springs make them impractical for most geothermal applications.
