The combined flow of the hot-springs system is estimated at about 200 lpm.
Water chemistry indicates that contamination with seawater near the surface is minimal.
If mixing of colder waters is taking place it occurs at deeper levels and may not involve seawater.
Comments The hot springs probably result from circulation of surface waters along deep-seated fractures in the country bedrock.
Chemical analysis indicates that the parent thermal waters may have a seawater -123-
