The values for nitrogen and oxygen probably represent air contamination because the proportions are almost those of air.
In addition, during analysis, gas pressure in the sampling tube was found to be very low, possibly due to equipment malfunction while acquiring the sample (W. Evans, pers. comm.)
* Despite these problems, the analysis shows clearly that methane is the major gas discharging with the thermal springs.
The late Tertiary sedimentary beds thought to underlie the area may be the source of this methanerich gas.
